RUSTENBURG – Two children, aged between nine and 11 and believed to be brothers, were killed when they were knocked down by a car on the N4 close to the Waterfall Mall in Rustenburg on Saturday, paramedics said. When ER24 arrived on the scene at 10.05am, both children were lying in the middle of the road, ER24 spokeswoman Ineke van Huyssteen said. “Unfortunately, the children were found not showing any signs of life and ER24 paramedics declared both the two boys dead on the scene.” The details surrounding the accident were not yet known, but local authorities were on the scene for further investigations, she said.
	  African News Agency